content.Setup Guide:
Follow the [Installation Guide](./INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md) to install dependencies and set up your environment.
- Make your changes and test locally to ensure they work as intended.
- Submit your pull request with a detailed description of your changes.

content.Introduction:
How to Contribute
Thank you for considering contributing to Hypothetical Repo!
Contributions help us grow and improve, and we appreciate your interest.
Please go through [Readme](./README.md) to get the project overview.
content.Bug Reporting: - Report Bugs: Found a bug? Create an issue with details such as steps to reproduce, expected behavior, and any relevant screenshots or logs.
content.Feature Proposals: - Submit Enhancements: Have a feature idea? Propose it in an issue. Be sure to explain the problem it solves and how it improves the project.
content.Pull Requests: - Pull Requests: Review the [Pull Request Template](./PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) for submitting your changes. Ensure your code is well-documented and adheres to our style guidelines.

content.Community Guidelines: Please adhere to our [Code of Conduct](./CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) to maintain a welcoming community. This ensures a respectful and collaborative environment for everyone.
